description: Lindy is a platform for building AI assistants that automate routine knowledge work across email, chat, and calendars.

name: AgentGPT
key_features: Browser-based agent deployment
Goal-driven task generation
Automatic task execution loop
Open-source Next.js + FastAPI stack
pricing_model: Open-source project; hosted version requires user-provided API keys and incurs usage costs.
description: AgentGPT is a web platform for assembling autonomous GPT agents.
long_description: Users name an agent and set a goal; the system iteratively creates and executes tasks with GPT-4 or GPT-3.5, displaying progress in a browser interface.

name: CAMEL
key_features: Large-scale multi-agent simulations up to millions of agents
Dynamic communication and role-playing between agents
Stateful memory for multi-step interactions
Automated data generation with tool integration
pricing_model: Open-source (Apache-2.0)

name: Salesforce Agentforce
key_features: Native Salesforce integration across CRM applications
Einstein Trust Layer for security and governance
Autonomous workflow execution with human handoff
Customizable actions via Flow and Apex
supported_models: Bring-your-own models such as OpenAI and Anthropic
pricing_model: Enterprise licensing through Salesforce Einstein 1 platform

name: Fixie.ai
key_features: Hosted agent runtime with API and chat integrations
Skill and knowledge base system for external data and APIs
Marketplace of pre-built skills and agents
Supports multiple LLM backends
Enterprise security and deployment options
pricing_model: Contact for pricing (free developer tier available)

name: BabyAGI
key_features: Autonomous task creation and prioritization
Function registry with dependency graph
Vector database memory for context
Dashboard for function management and logging
Open-source and extensible Python framework
pricing_model: Open-source project under MIT license.
description: BabyAGI is an experimental framework for building self-improving autonomous agents.
long_description: Originally released in 2023 as a minimalist LLM-powered task agent, BabyAGI now provides a function-based framework that registers, stores, and executes tasks with a dependency graph, persistent memory, and a web dashboard for monitoring and key management.

name: AgentVerse
key_features: Task-solving framework for collaborative multi-agent systems
Simulation framework for multi-agent environments
Supports local LLMs such as LLaMA and Vicuna
Demos including NLP Classroom, Prisoner's Dilemma, and Software Design
Extensible configuration of agents and environments
supported_models: Local LLMs like LLaMA and Vicuna
pricing_model: Free and open-source (Apache 2.0 license)

name: ChatDev
key_features: Virtual software company with multi-agent roles
Visualizer for observing real-time or replayed agent logs
Supports Git integration, Docker execution, and incremental development
Human-Agent Interaction mode for manual participation
MacNet framework for scalable DAG-style collaboration
pricing_model: Open-source (Apache-2.0), free
description: ChatDev is an open-source virtual software company where role-based agents collaborate to design, code, test, and document software.
long_description: Leveraging a MacNet-based pipeline, ChatDev coordinates specialized agents such as CEO, CTO, programmer, reviewer, tester, and designer. It integrates with Git and Docker, provides real-time log visualization, and supports human participation for customizable end-to-end software development.

name: Adept (ACT-1)
key_features: Translates natural language commands into actions across existing software
Observes the user interface to interact with web and desktop applications
Performs multi-step workflows such as navigating websites or filling forms
Learns from human demonstrations to improve task execution
pricing_model: Pricing not publicly disclosed (research project)

name: Semantic Kernel
key_features: Model-agnostic framework with connectors for OpenAI, Azure OpenAI, Hugging Face, and NVIDIA NIM.
Modular skill system combining native code, prompt templates, and plugins.
Planners for goal-based orchestration and multi-agent workflows.
Built-in memory and vector store connectors for context persistence.
Supports C#, Python, and Java with enterprise-ready tooling.
supported_models: Hugging Face and NVIDIA NIM models
Local models via Ollama, LM Studio, or ONNX
pricing_model: Open-source (Apache 2.0 license)

name: OpenAI Agents SDK (Swarm)
key_features: Lightweight Python framework for multi-agent workflows
Handoffs for transferring control between agents
Guardrails for input and output validation
Session management for conversation history
Tracing UI for debugging agent runs
Provider-agnostic design supporting 100+ LLMs
pricing_model: Open-source MIT license; pay for underlying model and compute usage.
description: OpenAI’s official agent SDK, formerly known as Swarm, providing minimal components to build custom LLM agents.
long_description: The Agents SDK offers agents, tools, handoffs, guardrails, sessions, and tracing to compose autonomous multi-agent applications. It integrates with OpenAI Responses and Chat Completions APIs and other models through LiteLLM.

name: SuperAGI
key_features: Provision, spawn, and deploy autonomous AI agents.
Extend agent capabilities with tools from a marketplace.
Graphical user interface and action console for agent interaction.
Multiple vector database integrations and agent memory storage.
Performance telemetry with optimized token usage.
pricing_model: Open-source; optional SuperAGI Cloud

name: IBM watsonx Orchestrate

No-code workflow builder with prebuilt skills
Connectors to enterprise apps such as Slack, Workday, and SAP

Auditable and secure integrations
supported_models: IBM Granite and other foundation models available via watsonx.ai
pricing_model: 30-day free trial, then commercial subscription
description: Enterprise platform for building AI-powered digital workers that automate workflows across business applications.
long_description: watsonx Orchestrate combines a no-code interface, prebuilt skills, and IBM foundation models to let users design digital workers that execute tasks in HR, CRM, ERP, and other systems. The platform offers a developer-focused ADK and local sandbox, with governance and audit features for enterprise deployments.

name: Pydantic AI
key_features: Model-agnostic support for providers like OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini, Deepseek, Ollama, Groq, Cohere and Mistral.
Built-in Pydantic validation for type-safe, structured responses.
Seamless integration with Pydantic Logfire for real-time monitoring and debugging.
Optional dependency injection system for delivering data and services to agents.
Supports streamed responses and graph-based workflow composition.
pricing_model: Open Source (MIT)

name: SAP Joule
key_features: AI copilot for SAP applications
Context-aware insights from SAP data
Natural language interface
Cross-application integration across SAP cloud solutions
Built on SAP Business Technology Platform
Security and compliance controls

Third-party models (e.g., OpenAI) through SAP's generative AI hub
pricing_model: Included with select SAP cloud subscriptions (details not public)

description: A personal AI assistant that engages in empathetic conversation over chat or voice.
long_description: Pi stands for "Personal Intelligence" and is developed by Inflection AI. It focuses on friendly, supportive dialogue and offers both text and voice interactions across web and mobile platforms.

key_features: Contextual chat across Windows, Edge, and Microsoft 365
Writes and summarizes content in Word, Outlook, and Teams
Generates images and code snippets
Data analysis in Excel with natural language

Available as desktop app and web side panel
pricing_model: Free tier, Copilot Pro, Copilot for Microsoft 365

Workflows for multi-agent orchestration
Backend connectors to multiple LLM providers
Tool integrations such as web search, weather, and code execution
Retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) system
Memory management strategies
Observability with events and logging

Caching for performance optimization

pricing_model: Open-source (Apache 2.0 license)
description: Open-source toolkit for building production-ready multi-agent systems in Python or TypeScript.
long_description: Bee Agent Framework provides modular components—agents, workflows, tools, memory, and more—to assemble and orchestrate complex AI applications without extensive coding.

name: AutoGPT
key_features: Autonomous task chaining
Tool and API integration
Memory management for context retention
Web browsing and information gathering
File operations and content creation
Self-prompting and task breakdown
pricing_model: Open-source (MIT) for classic components, cloud-hosted platform in closed beta.
description: AutoGPT is a platform for creating and managing continuous AI agents that automate complex workflows.
long_description: AutoGPT began as an experimental project to demonstrate autonomous GPT-4 operation, showcasing goal decomposition, tool use, memory and self-prompting. It has evolved into a platform for building, deploying and monitoring agents with benchmarking and UI support.
